<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>A knife-wielding man has been shot by police in a shopping centre car park.</p>

<p>The terrifying encounter occurred outside of Lilydale Market in northeast Melbourne on Tuesday morning.</p>

<p>Victoria Police were called to the marketplace after a man armed with a knife was reported on Hutchinson Street around 8.30am. </p>

<p>Victoria Police shot the man and he received an injury to his upper body.</p>

<p>He is receiving medical treatment at the scene.</p>

<p>Police and emergency services remain on the scene at Lilydale. </p>

<p>The incident is currently under investigation and is being overseen by Professional Standards Commands.</p>

<p>More to come </p>
